# Cashflow Expense Management - Implementation Walkthrough

## Overview

Successfully implemented full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) functionality for managing expenses and income entries in the Cashflow tab. Users can now add, edit, and delete cashflow entries directly from the UI.

## Features Implemented

### 1. Backend API Endpoints

Added three new API endpoints to support expense management:

- **PUT /api/cashflow/:id** - Update existing cashflow entry
- **DELETE /api/cashflow/:id** - Delete cashflow entry (with protection for bill-linked entries)
- Enhanced service layer with helper methods

### 2. Frontend Components

#### ExpenseFormModal Component
Created a reusable modal form component with:
- Type toggle (Income/Expense)
- Amount input with validation
- Description text area
- Date picker
- Form validation (positive amounts, no future dates)
- Support for both "add" and "edit" modes

#### Enhanced Cashflow Screen
Updated the Cashflow tab with:
- **Floating Action Button (FAB)** - Bottom-right "+" button to add new entries
- **Enhanced Entry Display** - Shows date, description, and amount for each entry
- **"From Bill" Badge** - Visual indicator for bill-linked entries
- **Edit/Delete Actions** - Inline buttons for manual entries
- **Loading States** - Visual feedback during operations
- **Error Handling** - User-friendly error messages

